primary_host.about:
Full-time Mum kept busy by my wee boy James (2 years old).

In the past I have enjoyed traveling to other people's Airbnb homes and hope to share the experiance of home from home in my flat in Edinburgh.

Hobbies include eating out (always much more relaxing than the daily cooking), swimming and spas, horse riding and history.

sectioned_description.access: The flat is located within a secure gated close off West Port.
sectioned_description.description:
Small penthouse flat set in a gated close in the heart of Edinburgh's Old Town. Most festival venues and city centre attractions are all within walking distance and if you are looking to visit somewhere further outside of the city centre we have a good bus service on our doorstep.

The communal balcony is fantastic place to watch Edinburgh Castle firework display.

The flat has a bright livingroom with three windows and a Scottish baronial turret looking up and down West Port. The livingroom has a double sofa bed, workspace for laptop and dining table.

The kitchen and bathroom have been recently updated. The bathroom has a large bath, over shower and underfloor heating perfect for those chilling Scottish mornings. The kitchen comes with tea, coffee with cafetiere, sugar, milk and biscuits, cereal for breakfast as well as all the basic essentials such as oil, salt and pepper. However if you prefer to take it easy there are many local restaurants nearby and Deliveroo and Just Eat food deliveries are available to the flat. There is also a local Sainsburys 2 mins from the flat on West Port.

The bedroom has a comfy double bed, large wardrobe with mirrors and alarm clock.  A hairdryer is also available. Please let me know if you require a toddler travel bed, highchair and baby monitor. 100% cotton linen and towels are provided as well as complimentary shampoo and body wash. An iron an mini ironing board are also included.

Good 4G mobile reception provided by the major UK netwoks. Wifi is only available by a BT wifi-pay as you go hotspot at a charge (ask for more details).

The flat is located within a secure gated close off West Port.

The flat has a good public transport service (taxis, buses and trams). 

You can get a dayticket for £4 any travel all day within the LRT bus zone. Singles cost £1.60.

Waverly Station: 4mins taxi / 13mins walking distance.

Edinburgh Airport: 20mins taxi oron the number 35 LRT bus route (only costs £1.60 from airport)/ tram available to Princes Street then 12min walk to flat.

NCP car park at Castle Terrace.

I love history and have many books available on Edinburgh's historical development over the centuries. Please let me know if you would like me to provide these books for your stay. Information on public transport and local attractions is available in the guest book.

sorted_reviews.comments:
Great apartment!! Stayed 3 days for the festival, lovely clean bright airy apartment, walking distance from station and all the sites. Would highly recommend staying here. Emma very kindly let us drop our bags off at the apartment at 1130 which was great.

Regards
Kathleen

Emma's place is a great place, close to some Fringe Venues and easy to get across Edinburgh. The place was clean and fresh and had everything needed for the three days we were there. I would highly recommend.

A perfectly located flat with an amazing view of the castle from the outdoor communal balcony . Emma was a lovely host, who was really easy to deal with and made our edinburgh festival experience that much more enjoyable for having stayed in her flat.

Great location, Emma was a great host. She was not around the weekend we stayed but her instructions were perfect and we felt well looked after: perfect for a weekend break in the centre of edinburgh.

Emmas place has a ridiculously great location, and situated at the very corner of the historical grassmarket with all it's pubs and restaurants it's the perfect place to stay for a weekend of exploring the city. When getting the hang of all the closes leading off the royal mile even New Town area is just a short 10-15 minutes walk away! 

The apartment was clean, tidy, in a charming setup below the castle and perfect for us, one couple and a single traveler. Both parties getting their own sleeping space. Having a nice and fresh kitchen was great for preparing a small breakfast before heading out. 

We didn't get to meet Emma in person nut she was very friendly answering all our questions (all though there wasn't many) and left us a personal welcome note with tips about the city and a bunch of folders to help us get started with our exploring. 

We would highly recommend staying in Emmas place if you get the chance!

Ellen

Excellent location and host! Everything tidy and as advertised. Only note I'd make is for other American travelers - we thought the lack of wifi wouldn't be a bother as we had a data package but the data stream was very poor for us, so we wished we had wifi. Not a problem with anything Emma did or the flat, but just something for future travelers to note. We would stay again though!

Emma's place is in an incredible location; you can walk all over Old Town from her flat. The only downside is that it does not have wi-fi but Emma's hospitality makes up for it. I would definetely recommend it.

phrases.community_commitment.faq.what_happens_if: What if I decline the commitment?
phrases.community_commitment.faq.answer_to_what_: If you decline the commitment, you won’t be able to host or book using Airbnb, and you have the option to cancel your account. Once your account is cancelled, future booked trips will be cancelled. You will still be able to browse Airbnb but you won’t be able to book any reservations or host any guests.

phrases.community_commitment.important_step_towa: This commitment is an important step towards creating a global community where everyone can truly belong. Discrimination prevents hosts, guests, and their families from feeling included and welcomed, and we have no tolerance for it. Building an Airbnb where everyone can belong hinges on knowing that everyone in our community understands this mission and agrees to help us achieve it.
